<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Memory-Leak on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/memory-leak/</link><description>Recent content in Memory-Leak on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/memory-leak/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Memory Leak — Valgrind Lost Bytes / Still Reachable Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-memory-leak--valgrind-lost-bytes--still-reachable-fix"&gt;[Solution] C Memory Leak — Valgrind Lost Bytes / Still Reachable Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;memory leak&lt;/strong&gt; occurs when your program allocates heap memory (via &lt;code&gt;malloc&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;calloc&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;realloc&lt;/code&gt;) but fails to &lt;code&gt;free()&lt;/code&gt; it before the pointer is lost. Valgrind reports this as &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;definitely lost: N bytes in M blocks&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;still reachable: N bytes&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;. While small leaks may be harmless in short-lived programs, large or repeated leaks exhaust memory and cause performance degradation or crashes.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Valgrind: memory leak detected</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak-valgrind/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak-valgrind/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="valgrind-memory-leak-detected"&gt;Valgrind: memory leak detected&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A memory leak occurs when allocated memory is never freed. Valgrind reports lost blocks with stack traces showing where each allocation was made.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Forgetting to free
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;leak&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// never free(p)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Early return without free
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;process&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;buf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (error_condition) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// buf leaked
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(buf);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Lost pointer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; NULL; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// can&amp;#39;t free anymore
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-free-all-allocations"&gt;Fix 1: Free all allocations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;no_leak&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ... use p ...
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(p);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-cleanup-pattern"&gt;Fix 2: Use cleanup pattern&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;process&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;buf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;malloc&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;buf) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;do_work&lt;/span&gt;(buf);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;free&lt;/span&gt;(buf); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// always free
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; result;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-track-with-valgrind"&gt;Fix 3: Track with Valgrind&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;gcc -g -o prog prog.c
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;valgrind --leak-check&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;full --show-leak-kinds&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;all ./prog
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Basic leak check&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;valgrind --leak-check&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;full ./prog
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Full report with summaries&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;valgrind --leak-check&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;full --show-leak-kinds&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;definite,possible ./prog
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Output example:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ==12345== 100 bytes in 1 blocks are definitely lost&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ==12345== at 0x4C2AB80: malloc (in /usr/lib/valgrind/vgpreload_memcheck-amd64-linux.so)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ==12345== by 0x108674: main (leak.c:5)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/double-free-heap/"&gt;Double free&lt;/a&gt; — freeing twice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/use-after-free-heap/"&gt;Use after free&lt;/a&gt; — accessing freed memory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/out-of-memory-malloc/"&gt;Out of memory: malloc failed&lt;/a&gt; — malloc failure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ Valgrind - memory error detected</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/valgrind-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/valgrind-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="valgrind---memory-error-detected"&gt;Valgrind - memory error detected&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Valgrind&amp;rsquo;s Memcheck tool detects memory errors including leaks, invalid reads/writes, and use of uninitialized memory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Memory leak
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// forgot delete[]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Invalid read
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;delete&lt;/span&gt; p;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printf(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;%d&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// invalid read
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Uninitialized value
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; x;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printf(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;%d&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, x); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// use of uninitialized value
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-run-valgrind"&gt;Fix 1: Run Valgrind&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;g++ -g -o prog prog.cpp
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;valgrind --leak-check&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;full ./prog
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-fix-reported-leaks"&gt;Fix 2: Fix reported leaks&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ... use p ...
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;delete&lt;/span&gt;[] p; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// free memory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-fix-invalid-access"&gt;Fix 3: Fix invalid access&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;p; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// read before delete
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;delete&lt;/span&gt; p;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// don&amp;#39;t access p after this
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/sanitizers-address/"&gt;AddressSanitizer&lt;/a&gt; — faster detection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/sanitizers-memory/"&gt;MemorySanitizer&lt;/a&gt; — uninitialized memory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak-valgrind/"&gt;C: Memory leak&lt;/a&gt; — memory leaks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Java OutOfMemoryError: Java Heap Space Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/outofmemory-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/java/outofmemory-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="outofmemoryerror-java-heap-space"&gt;OutOfMemoryError: Java Heap Space&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when the JVM cannot allocate enough memory for a new object because the heap is full and garbage collection cannot free sufficient space. This is an &lt;code&gt;Error&lt;/code&gt; (not an &lt;code&gt;Exception&lt;/code&gt;), meaning the JVM considers it unrecoverable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The JVM heap stores all object instances. When the heap fills up and GC can&amp;rsquo;t reclaim enough space, the OOME fires. The default heap size varies by JVM but is typically 256MB-1GB.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin OutOfMemoryError — Heap Memory Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/outofmemory-kotlin/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/outofmemory-kotlin/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="outofmemoryerror--heap-memory-exhausted"&gt;OutOfMemoryError — Heap Memory Exhausted&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;OutOfMemoryError&lt;/code&gt; occurs when the JVM cannot allocate more objects because the heap is full.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The JVM heap stores all objects. When too many objects are created and not garbage collected, the heap fills up. This is common with large collections, memory leaks, or excessive allocation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Large collections&lt;/strong&gt; — loading too much data into memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Memory leaks&lt;/strong&gt; — objects not being garbage collected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bitmap/Image processing&lt;/strong&gt; — large image buffers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;String concatenation&lt;/strong&gt; — building huge strings inefficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Large collection
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; hugeList = (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;.MAX_VALUE).toList() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// OutOfMemoryError
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Memory leak
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Cache&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;companion&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;object&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; data = mutableMapOf&amp;lt;String, Any&amp;gt;() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Never cleared
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Cache&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;key&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;] = ByteArray(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt; * &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// 1MB
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: String concatenation in loop
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; result = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;repeat(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000000&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Creates many intermediate strings
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Large array allocation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; array = IntArray(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;.MAX_VALUE / &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// OutOfMemoryError
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-lazy-loading"&gt;Fix 1: Use lazy loading&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; hugeList = loadAllData() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Loads everything
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; data = loadPage(pageNumber) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Load only what&amp;#39;s needed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-clear-collections"&gt;Fix 2: Clear collections&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Cache&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; data = mutableMapOf&amp;lt;String, Any&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Cache&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; data = mutableMapOf&amp;lt;String, Any&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;clear&lt;/span&gt;() = &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;.clear()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-stringbuilder"&gt;Fix 3: Use StringBuilder&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; result = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;repeat(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000000&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; sb = StringBuilder()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;repeat(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000000&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sb.append(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; result = sb.toString()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-streams-for-large-data"&gt;Fix 4: Use streams for large data&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; list = (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10000000&lt;/span&gt;).toList() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Large list in memory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; sum = (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10000000&lt;/span&gt;).sum() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Process without storing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Memory-efficient processing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;processLargeFile&lt;/span&gt;(path: String) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; File(path).bufferedReader().useLines { lines &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; lines.forEach { line &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; process(line)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Proper cleanup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ImageCache&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; cache = mutableMapOf&amp;lt;String, Bitmap&amp;gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get&lt;/span&gt;(key: String): Bitmap? {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; cache[key]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;put&lt;/span&gt;(key: String, bitmap: Bitmap) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (cache.size &amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; cache.clear() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Simple eviction
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; cache[key] = bitmap
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;clear&lt;/span&gt;() = cache.clear()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/stack-overflow/"&gt;StackOverflowError&lt;/a&gt; — infinite recursion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/concurrent-modification/"&gt;ConcurrentModificationException&lt;/a&gt; — concurrent access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/io-exception/"&gt;IOException&lt;/a&gt; — I/O operation failed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>State update error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/frameworks/react-native/state-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/frameworks/react-native/state-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when React Native attempts to update the state of a component that has already been unmounted, typically during async operations. This was a common source of memory leaks and warnings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Async operation (fetch, setTimeout) completes after component unmounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Event listener not cleaned up in &lt;code&gt;useEffect&lt;/code&gt; return&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigating away from a screen while a request is in progress&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not using an &lt;code&gt;isMounted&lt;/code&gt; check or abort controller&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use cleanup functions in &lt;code&gt;useEffect&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-jsx" data-lang="jsx"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useEffect&lt;/span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;react&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ActivityIndicator&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;View&lt;/span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;react-native&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;UserList&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;users&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setUsers&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;([]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;loading&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setLoading&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;);
